    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1997 Porsche 911 Carrera, the pinnacle of air-cooled engineering. This specimen features the M64 flat-six engine equipped with the Varioram induction system, providing a broad torque curve and visceral throttle response. Power is delivered through a G50 six-speed manual transaxle with precise shift gates and an original limited-slip differential. The chassis retains its factory-spec multi-link rear suspension and ventilated four-piston monobloc calipers, offering unparalleled mechanical feedback. This vehicle has been kept in a climate-controlled environment, showing zero evidence of oil seepage or bushing fatigue. A definitive turn-key example for the purist collector.",
